## Overview

Omni Sentinal is a full-stack penetration testing operations platform that automates and centralises the entire pentest workflow — from initial recon through exploitation to reporting. It exposes a REST API backed by a React dashboard, with every feature accessible both programmatically and from the UI.

It is designed primarily for **Hack The Box** and CTF engagements but is fully capable of supporting professional pentests.

### What it does

| Phase | Capabilities |
|-------|-------------|
| **Recon** | Nmap scanning, banner grabbing, SMB/SNMP/LDAP enumeration, DNS/subdomain brute-force, OSINT (Shodan, GreyNoise, crt.sh, BGPView, WHOIS, and more) |
| **Web** | Directory busting, XSS, SQLi, SSTI, GraphQL fuzzing, JWT inspection/forging, file upload bypass, open redirect, CORS misconfiguration |
| **Exploitation** | CVE lookup, searchsploit, Metasploit RPC, reverse shell catcher, file transfer one-liners, TTY upgrade sequences |
| **Post-Exploit** | Auto LinPEAS/WinPEAS via SSH, privilege escalation checklists, loot organiser, credential tracker |
| **Intelligence** | CVE-to-exploit chaining, port-based methodology suggestions, Ollama AI attack narrative generation, CVE heatmap |
| **Reporting** | PDF/Markdown reports, HTB-specific report templates, Obsidian vault export |
| **Operations** | Scheduled recurring scans, webhook alerts (Slack/Discord), scan diffing, per-scan timelines |

