## Usage

### Starting a Scan

**Via the UI:** Click **New Scan**, enter an IP or hostname, optionally enable Aggressive mode, add tags, and click **Start Scan**.

**Via the API:**
```bash
# Get a token
TOKEN=$(curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8000/auth/token \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"username":"admin","password":"YOUR_PASSWORD","role":"admin"}' \
  | jq -r .access_token)

# Start a scan
curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8000/scans \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"target":"10.10.10.1","aggressive":false,"tags":["htb"]}'
```

### Checking Scan Status

```bash
curl -s http://localhost:8000/scans/$SCAN_ID \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" | jq .status
```

