## Development

### Running Without Docker

```bash
cd ~/omni-sentinal

# Install Python deps
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Start Redis
redis-server --daemonize yes

# Start Celery worker
celery -A core.worker:app worker --concurrency=2 --loglevel=info &

# Start API
uvicorn dashboard.app:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --reload

# Start UI (separate terminal)
cd ~/omni-ui
npm install
npm run dev
```

### Running Preflight Checks

```bash
./"Install command" --check-only
```

This validates that all required system commands (`python3`, `pip3`, `git`, `node`, `npm`, `curl`, `nmap`, `openssl`, `docker`) are available without writing any files.

### Project Conventions

- All plugins go in `~/omni-sentinal/plugins/` as standalone `.py` files
- Plugin names must match `^[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*$`
- All API routes are authenticated with JWT (`verify_token`) or require admin (`require_admin`)
- Database writes use parameterised SQLite queries — never string formatting
- Long-running operations are dispatched to Celery workers, never blocking the API

